<p><b>Indigenous 
</b></p>
<p><b>peoples;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Alleged imminent threat of eviction faced by the Sengwer indigenous people. 
</p>
<p>According to the information received, police are poised to forcibly evict Sengwer 
</p>
<p>indigenous people from their homes in the Embobut Forest area. For centuries, the 
</p>
<p>Sengwer indigenous people, also known as the Cherangany indigenous people, have 
</p>
<p>lived, hunted and gathered in the Embobut Forest area in the Rift Valley of Kenya. 
</p>
<p>Sengwer continue to live in or near the Embobut Forest and to engage in cultural and 
</p>
<p>subsistence practices in the area. According to reports, police forces have been 
</p>
<p>gathering in the Embobut Forest area in preparation of evictions ordered by the 
</p>
<p>Government in pursuit of forest and water conservation objectives. Sources report that 
</p>
<p>since the 1970s Kenyan authorities have made repeated attempts to forcibly evict the 
</p>
<p>Sengwer from the forest for resettlement in other areas.  
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
