<p>Allegations concerning the physical and psychological integrity of a human rights 
</p>
<p>defender in pre-trial detention.  According to the information received, since 22 June 
</p>
<p>2012, Mr. Hilal Mammadov had been in pre-trial detention under charges of, inter alia, 
</p>
<p>treason and incitement to national, racial or religious hostility. It is reported that in 
</p>
<p>November 2012, Mr. Mammadov was beaten and injured by his cell mate who allegedly 
</p>
<p>suffered from a serious mental disease.  It is also reported that, in November 2012, the 
</p>
<p>courts rejected a complaint filed by Mr. Mammadov denouncing acts of torture and ill-
</p>
<p>treatment he allegedly suffered during his arrest, acts which were reportedly supported 
</p>
<p>by a forensic examination.  Mr. Mammadov has been a leader of Azerbaijan&#8217;s ethnic 
</p>
<p>Talysh minority and had shortly before his arrest become editor of the newspaper 
</p>
<p>Tolishi Sado (Talysh Voice), the only newspaper published in the Talysh minority 
</p>
