<p>AGO 4/2013 
</p>
<p><b>Angola  
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p><b>Summary 
</b></p>
<p><b>executions;  
</b></p>
<p><b>Violence against 
</b></p>
<p><b>women;   
</b></p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>Allegations of sorcery-related killings. According to the information received, on 5 May 
</p>
<p>2013, Ms Visalta Kuricanza Paulo Muacahia, a 57 year old peasant, was found dead 
</p>
<p>nearby the Tafe River, in Cafunfo, Lunda Norte Province. Her body was naked and tied 
</p>
<p>up, her genitals mutilated and her face and legs burnt. On 7 May 2013 a similar killing 
</p>
<p>was reported in the area of Tchimango. Ms Aida Sanehena, aged 47, was hanged near a 
</p>
<p>mining area. Her face and some body parts were also burnt. According to reports, two 
</p>
<p>other killings of a similar nature have been reported, on 8 December 2012, and on 14 
</p>
<p>April 2013 
</p>
<p>10/01/2014 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
